WIMBLEDON
June 25, 2001
Carlos Moya
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
THE MODERATOR:  Questions, please. 
 
 
Q.  You played really well today.  You came back after two sets. 
 
CARLOS MOYA:  Yes.  
 
Q.  Did you feel more comfortable on grass? 
 
CARLOS MOYA:  Well, at the beginning not really, because I was playing serve and volley.  Today was very hot, it was not that fast, and it didn't help me.  After I was two sets to Love down, I tried to change my game and I stayed at the baseline.  And I think was better for me because it was when I started to win.   I'm very happy the way I played because it's not my favourite surface.  But I come here every year, I do my best, and sometimes I win matches, which is very good.  
 
Q.  You were also playing serve and volley when you were winning.  You seemed to be much more comfortable with your serve and volley?
 
CARLOS MOYA:  Yeah, I feel comfortable when I serve and volley.  Is what I've been doing the last year here on grass.  I didn't win many matches, but at least I played the game I have to play to win matches here.  I tried to adapt to the surface, which is very difficult for me.  You know, I'm just doing my best, doing all what I can.  And it's great to see that after a great battle like today you finally won.  
 
Q.  Absolutely.  Have you been doing more preparation on grass this year? 
 
CARLOS MOYA:  Well, I played in Halle two weeks ago.  I lost first round and I stayed there for a few days to practise there.  And before here, I could not practise on grass, but I got here a few days before and, you know, I had some practise and, you know, it was good.  
 
Q.  You're looking good today. 
 
CARLOS MOYA:  Thank you, thank you.  
 

End of FastScripts....

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT